name: SONY ACTION CAM HDR-AS30V ( Version 2 )  - BUNDLE
description:
Sony Action Cam HDR-AS30V is Sony's entry into the action camera/POV market. Revisions to the first version lead to this 2nd version, the HDR-AS30V. With a Exmor R CMOS Sensor and Carl Ziess lens, it has exceptional image quality  and great low light performance. It shoots in full HD with your choice of 60P, 50P, 30P and 25P, wide or medium angle and it has a true Super Slow Motion mode.  Great battery life and class leading reliability combined with great value make this the perfect camera for all types of extreme sports, motorsports or for just every day use.

It is the official onboard camera for Australian Drifting GP and Motive DVD.  To celebrate becoming an official Sony Action Cam dealer, we are offering the below promotion.

name: 2013 WORLD TIME ATTACK  - MOTIVE DVD #20
description:
**** DISCOUNT PRE ORDER******
****DELIVERIES START LATE JANUARY. GOES ON SALE AT NEWSAGENTS LATE FEBRUARY*****

Motive DVD #20 has full event coverage of the 2013 Yokohama World Time Attack Challenge. Go behind the scenes and see what happens in the pits, talk with the drivers and take a closer look at some of the top cars. There is also onboards in the fastest cars and plenty of action from both around the track and in the pits. 2 hours of time attack action!

Also covers the Turbosmart Flying 500 as well as on and off track entertainment.

name: Motive DVD #19
description:
Motive DVD #19 features the 2013 Castrol Edge GT-R Challenge and Drag Battle. This year was out biggest and fiercest competition with every record broken. 38 competitors in total, means there is over 80 minutes of action from the runway! 

As well as the Cootamundra Airport madness, there is project cars, new car review and more.



Hi-Tec Oils Figure-8 Drift Series Rd1&2 - Sydney Motorsport Park
Toyota FT86 New Car Review - Believe the hype?
Motive Garage - R32 GT-R Brake and power upgrades

2013 Castrol Edge GT-R Challenge - 11 of the fastest street GT-Rs in Oz
2103 Castrol Edge Drag BAttle - Our biggest and best to date!
Nitto - Genuine 9-second street car with 1000+whp

description: New for 2013/14 is the "NITTO" special edition T-Shit. Nitto won the 2013 Castrol Edge  GT-R Challenge and Drag Battle. A genuine 9.2-second street car with over 1000whp, it is certainly worth wearing.

name: Motive DVD #16
description:
Motive DVD #16 has nearly an hour of runway madness as the 2012 GT-R Challenge and Motive Drag Battle hit Cootamundra airport. Australia's fastest and quickest street cars go crazy with 150mph+ quarter mile passes, powerskids and plenty of drag action. The stage was also set for a great GT-R showdown with JUN, RH9GTR, the Powertune R34 and the 101 Motorsport R32 GT-R all in the same place at the same time! There is also plenty of laughs with Denzo, Motive Garage, some US action and a whole lot more.

Old School Cool – Denzo’s GC10 Skyline
The Lowdown presents Showcased
JPC Tour – The new “off-lips” shop

description:
Motive DVD #15 brings you all the action from the 2011 WTAC event at Eastern Creek Raceway. There is a feature on the Yokohama World Time Attack Challenge covering Pro, Open and Clubsprint Class, the Tectaloy International Drift Challenge and a documentary following our campaign in JET200.With on-boards, interviews and more, we take you inside the world’s biggest and best time attack event as Australia’s, Japan’s and the USA’s fastest cars go head to head. All this, and a whole lot more, in 2-hours of jam-packed action. Motive DVD, the world’s leading performance import DVD.

description: Working with DSPORT Magazine in the USA, we've shot so much great footage that we can't fit it all in Motive DVD, so, we put together this special edition DVD called Japan vs USA. Workshop visits, car features and drag events from the USA and Japan. Which country does it better? Watch and find out.

name: Motive DVD #14
description:
2011 JUST CAR INSURANCE AUSTRALIAN DRIFTING GRAND PRIX & TRACK BATTLE AUSTRALIAN TIME ATTACK SERIES OFFICIAL DVD

Motive DVD #14 is a special collectors edition with full coverage of the 2012 Just Car Insurance Australian Drifting Grand Prix and the Track Battle Australian Time Attack Series. All of the drifting action form qualifying to battles and the extreme entry comp are covered, along with driver interviews and a host of on-board cameras. There is also exclusive coverage of the Track Battle Australian Time Attack Series, run in conjunction with ADGP events, from Round 1 at the Calder Park Thunderdome in Victoria, Round 2 at Queensland Raceway and Round 3 at Barbagallo Raceway in WA. Make sure you also check out the hilarious bloopers and behind the scenes coverage. All filmed and edited to Motive DVD’s high standards and set to a pumping music score. 2 hours of action for only of $14.95

name: Motive DVD #13
description:
Motive DVD #13 continues to bring the best performance import automotive action. There is car features on a aero top big-single-turbo Supra, Banger's 4-door R34 drift car and Buschur Racing's 9-second street evo.

There is a massive 30-minute Motive 2011 Drag Battle feature, coverage of Drift Attack at Winton, JET200 hits the track for it's first shakedown, Sydney Jamboree coverage and a whole lot more.

There is something for everyone in this issue

name: Motive DVD #012
description:
Motive DVD #12 see's Nigel Petrie's Engineered to Slide 180SX take centre stage along with Shane's super clean RBWARE R32 GT-R. We also feature Benjo's S13.5 and for Motive Garage we have the "Pimp my Wife's Ride" special along with the engine build for JET200.

We hit Powercruise Perth, the Twilight Sprint Series, a wild track day at Barbagallo and we have the Driftapalooza at Eastern Creek. Can't have too much of a good thing!

name: Motive DVD #011
description:
Motive DVD #11 contains our first Drag Battle at Cootamundra Airport. PJ's mental 9-second S13 takes on all comers on the runway for an epic shootout!

There is also car features on the JPC R35 GT-R, a 1000+hp V6 S13 Silvia, Ryan's Track Spec Evo VI and more. We also visit an SAUSA track day, a Hardtuned.net cruise, the R32 GT-R 21st Anniversary cruise, Powercruise 25 and more again!

Motive Garage has a feature on a twin turbo upgrade to an R35 GT-R and we hang out with Denzo at JPC for some laughs.

description: Complete your collection and save some money by purchasing Motive DVD Box Set #1. The pack contains Motive DVD #1-#5. The R.R.P. of $50.00 is a saving of nearly $25 over buying them individually. With nearly 10 hours of awesome performance automotive content, it offers great value for money

name: JET200 T-Shirt
description: JET200 is Motive DVD's long term project car and is a dedicated time attack machine. WIth a full high quality screen print of the car, this t-shirt is a must for JET200 and Silvia fans.

name: Drift Central 4 DVD
description: Kick it old school with Drift Central 4 DVD. It has full coverage of the 2008 Toyo Tyres Drift Australia Series as well as driver features on Luke Fink and Trent Whyte just to name a few. Classic drifting action!

name: Motive DVD #010
description:
Motive DVD #010 set the benchmark for Motive DVD with the best cinematography, editing and action to date. 

Its contains the 2010 GT-R Challenge at Cootamundra airpot where some of the toughest street GT-Rs in Australia battled it out.

Clint's street R32 from WA is on the cover and the DVD is filled with performance import action!

name: Motive DVD #009
description:
Motive DVD #9 front cover car is a mental widebody RX-7 street car. We also check out a 9-second Evo from the US and there is the DSPORT 2011 New Car Buyers guide as well.

We have some fun at Trav's annual demo derby birthday bash and we have highlights from the 2010 Yokohama World Time Attack Challenge.

We also take our S13 circuit racing and show you how you can do it to.

name: Motive DVD #008
description:
Motive DVD #008 is once again filled with the best action form Australia, the USA and Japan. The cover car is  a 90second street and strip Evo from AMS and there is car features on a clean street S14 from WA and Pac Performance's RX-3 drag car.

We attend some of the best events in Oz including Auto X, Compak Attak and Powercruise Sydney. We also visit Buschur Racing and Top Secret!

name: Motive DVD #007
description:
Motive DVD #007 is the Japan Special. We check out the best the land of the rising sun has to offer while on the DSPORT Tokyo Autosalon Tour.
- Tokyo Autosalon
- RB26 TUning Anniversary
- D1GP demo round
- DSPORT Drift Experience at Fuji Speedway
- NOB Tanaguchi's Vertex S15
- Daikoku Futo
- Motive Garage JET200 progress
- Croydon Racing Developments Tour

name: Motive DVD #006
description:
Motive DVD #006 has action form both Australia and the USA. 
Two R35 GT-R feature cars from SoCal,
 Redline TIme Attack, 
Tyler McQuarrie and the Falken Tyre 350Z,
 R35 GT-R time attack car, 
back stage at Top Gear Live, 
Antilag cruise in Perth
Modball Rally SoCal
Oran Park Raceway farewell private drift day
and more!

name: Motive DVD #005
description:
Motive DVD #005 sees the Godfather of Drift, Danny :"Denzo" Vahoumis, take over with his 600hp "off-lips" RB powered Silvia. We also go on a tour of JPC with plenty of laughs on the way.

SEMA 2009 footage, Powercruise Perth, Motive Garage, Texas Supra Meet, Import Drag Racing Circuit, Redline Time Attack, Formula D FInals and more!

Drift, Drag, Street, Circuit....which ones's your motive?

name: Motive DVD #004
description:
Motive DVD #4 is the Evo vs WRX special. We feature two of the top time attack cars from each camp, the Cusco/Tomei WRX and the Sierra Sierra Evo. We also check out the Evo vs WRX Challenge, Ken Block Gymkhana 2 launch party, Silver Bullet Sti and Grudge Match 3 between the Ralliart and WRX.

There is also drifting action with Project D and the Motive Garage S13 plus some hot first date model features.

name: Motive DVD #003
description: Motive DVD #3 is the GT-R special. We hold out first GT-R Challenge at Cootamundra airport with some of the fastest GT-Rs in Australia. We also check out Tokyo Autosalon, some Australian cruising, SEMA and the R34 10th Anniversary cruise. We also feature a 9-second GT-R in the USA and one of the world's fastest true steet GT-Rs, JUN, and a whole lot more.

name: Motive DVD #002
description: Motive DVD 2 has full coverage of the 2009 Superlap held at Oran Park. Australia;s best time attack cars do battle to see who is the fastest. there is also a feature on Robert Marjan's DEVLSH 200SX, the fastest Silvia drag car in the world. There is also a feature on Project D, Powercruise Eastern Creek and the first Motive Garage with JET200

name: Motive DVD #001 - Red Bull Drifting World Championships
description:
The very first Motive DVD covers all the action from the Redbull Drifting World Championship, including going behind the scenes with Australian drivers Luke Fink and Leighton Fine. All the battles, all the drama and all the fun.

There is also a feature on street drifting in Japan with the legendary Team Burst. A must for drifting fans.

name: Drifters Unleashed DVD
description:
Words can't describe just how crazy this DVD is. Think Krusty Demons of Dirt meets drifting. We hired Oran Park Raceway and invited the best drivers in Australia to come have some fun with no judges, no rules and no limits.

This is some of the best drifting action you'll ever see.
